    "ts": "1738200838.829399",
    "client_msg_id": "673058b4-922c-474e-b456-f063060df2b5",
    "text": "I have been moaning about the under-utilization of zoom and visual nesting for a long time, and this is a really nice low overhead approach. Are there downsides? It feels like needing to recalculate for every element in the DOM, regardless of whether it is in the viewport, is going to slow things down when you get to a certain volume of elements, maybe?",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1738192302.196989",
    "parent_user_id": "U0378MDUG1Y",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "Ju8vS",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I have been moaning about the under-utilization of zoom and visual nesting for a long time, and this is a really nice low overhead approach. Are there downsides? It feels like needing to recalculate for every element in the DOM, regardless of whether it is in the viewport, is going to slow things down when you get to a certain volume of elements, maybe?"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "two-minute-week",
    "channel_id": "C0120A3L30R"
  },
  {
    "user": "U0378MDUG1Y",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1738204921.390299",
    "edited": {
      "user": "U0378MDUG1Y",
      "ts": "1738205739.000000"
    },
    "client_msg_id": "e7ab181a-1552-4340-a0e0-a704c09e9938",
    "text": "I'd like to have a better grasp of where that threshold is, but I'm not sure at the moment. There's a good amount of low-hanging optimizations:\n\n• What properties are being animated? Need to be careful about properties that cause large reflows like width/height/font-size. Properties like opacity, translate, scale, etc. should be consistently performant.\n• If possible, applying <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/contain|contains> properties to each element can really help browsers optimize rendering/layout. Some simple testing I've done shows that this could cut rendering time by 2-3x.\n• I want to build primitive(s) that don't render offscreen elements. We may even be able to do it with just CSS using <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/content-visibility|content-visibility>.\n• In the future, <https://scroll-driven-animations.style/|scroll-driven animations> could potentially provide performance benefits since it's running off the main thread (I think browsers have a dedicated thread for scrolling) and zooming usually hijacks the `wheel` event.\n• It should be possible to hide (i.e. `display: none`) elements that are too scaled out in the near future with CSS `if()`\nIt's going to require some care, but I'm (currently) optimistic this can scale pretty well.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1738192302.196989",
    "parent_user_id": "U0378MDUG1Y",
